## Delegation — main session orchestrates, teammates do

The main conversation routes work to teammates instead of executing code-touching changes directly. The main session's job is to plan, brief, and decide.

**Default routing:**

| Task | Teammate |
|------|----------|
| File reads, searches, codebase exploration | `{{AGENT_PREFIX}}-explorer` |
| Single-file or small multi-file edits (1–3 files) | `{{AGENT_PREFIX}}-builder` |
| Lint / type-check / pre-merge quality pass | `{{AGENT_PREFIX}}-reviewer` |
| Dev-server lifecycle / local preview / port hygiene | `{{AGENT_PREFIX}}-server-minder` |
| Multi-file architectural work (4+ files, new abstractions) | `{{AGENT_PREFIX}}-architect` _(optional add-on)_ |
| Diagnosing a specific reported bug | `{{AGENT_PREFIX}}-debugger` _(optional add-on)_ |

**Minimal roster** = explorer + builder + reviewer + server-minder. Add `architect` + `debugger` only when the site outgrows simple.

**Teammates, not plain agents.** Spawn into a team via `Agent(team_name=...)` so teammates can `SendMessage` and persist. Use a fresh, date-stamped team name per session shaped like `{{TEAM_PREFIX}}-YYYYMMDD-<slug>`. NEVER reuse a bare team name — it accumulates ghost teammates.

**Reviewer pairing for every code-change teammate.** Pipeline: writer → reviewer sign-off → user sign-off → merge.

**Stall prevention — first action read-only.** Every writer-style teammate brief must close with this clause verbatim:

> FIRST ACTION: read-only diagnostic (pwd, git status, Read, Grep, or Glob) followed by SendMessage to team-lead with the output and your plan. THEN heartbeat at the start of every subsequent turn before any potentially-blocking tool call.

