## Branch Model

- **Production = `origin/main`**, served by {{HOST}}. Never push to main or deploy from the orchestrator.
- **Feature / experiment SITE code** branches off `origin/main` as `feat|fix|content|docs|chore/<scope>`, in its own worktree when parallel isolation helps. {{HOST}} builds {{PREVIEW_MECHANISM}} for every pushed branch — that preview is our isolation/staging mechanism. **There is no separate staging branch or tier.**
- **Dev-config is NOT a deployed artifact — don't branch it for "isolation."** `.claude/agents/`, `CLAUDE.md`, docs, and tooling are read from the working tree, never shipped. Commit them straight to the current working branch; branching them only creates merge-back busywork.
- **Worktree pattern:** `git -C {{REPO_PATH}} worktree add -b <type>/<scope> {{REPO_PATH}}-<slug> origin/main`.

_General cross-project version of these rules lives in the agent-templates library at `anthropic/shared/cross-project-rules.md`, and (once hydrated) in your global `~/.claude/CLAUDE.md` → "Worktree, write-target & dev-server discipline."_

