## Dev Servers & Previews

- **A persistent owner runs local dev servers — `{{AGENT_PREFIX}}-server-minder` (or the main session) — never transient writer agents.** Writers request a preview URL; they don't spawn their own long-lived `{{DEV_CMD}}`.
- **The dev server silently falls back when a port is taken** (`:{{DEV_PORT_BASE}}` → `:{{DEV_PORT_BASE}}+1` → …). The owner reports the EXACT "Local:" URL printed, never the requested port. Before relaying a dev URL to the user or diagnosing a failure on it, the orchestrator probes it (`curl` → expect 200) and confirms which process is actually listening.

_General cross-project version lives in the agent-templates library at `anthropic/shared/cross-project-rules.md`, and (once hydrated) in your global `~/.claude/CLAUDE.md` → "Worktree, write-target & dev-server discipline."_

